@lindsayad PETSc user manual has the following statement, "A large suite of routines is available for using geometric multigrid as a preconditioner"
It appears, though, that the implementation of this methodology is more involved than using predefined syntax. They follow on with the statement, "A multigrid preconditioner is created with the four commands
KSPCreate(MPI_Comm comm,KSP *ksp);
KSPGetPC(KSP ksp,PC *pc);
PCSetType(PC pc,PCMG);
PCMGSetLevels(pc,PetscInt levels,MPI_Comm *comms);
A large number of parameters affect the multigrid behavior."
I was not sure if the above steps have been coded into moose, allowing the moose user access to the multigrid methods referred to.
